<hl>
<seg id=1> An American transnational corporation will open 300 chain supermarkets in Fujian. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Xiamen, 16 January, by Yu Yingrui Two supermarkets named "Pei Shun" began doing business today. </seg>
<seg id=3> It marked the beginning of Xiamen Flanply Supermarket Ltd. in which Bichunse Corporation of an American transnational corporation held 60% share. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In Fujian Province, Xiamen Flanply Supermarket Ltd. was the first retail joint adventure cooperated by American Bichunse International Industry Groups, Chinese Xiamen Foreign Supply General Company, and Philippine Phili International Company. </seg>
<seg id=5> According to the agreement, the total investment of the project was US$26 million. The first-term investment was US$10 million to build 20 model chain shops and a modern delivery center. Then in accordance with the market situation, 300 chain shops would be opened gradually in nine towns and cities of Fujian Province. </seg>
<seg id=6> These shops were located in densely populated areas. Their size was about 400 square meters, and dealt in daily necessities and food that had a direct bearing on people's daily life. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> American Bichunse International Industry Groups was a large food transnational corporation whose annual total sales exceeded US$2,100 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> China acted with caution on opening Chinese retail business. Now there were pilot projects only in Beijing, Qingdao, Daling, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Wuhan, Shanghai, etc. The chain-shop development plan of American Bichunse International Industry Groups in China was a fairly big act of Chinese retail business using foreign capital. </seg>
</p>
